name: dialogue_subtext_pass
version: 1.0
description: >
  Rewrite dialogue to carry power, misalignment, and subtext; reduce exposition
  and remove 'on-the-nose' emotional labeling.
inputs:
  required:
    - chapter_draft
steps:
  - Identify dialogue lines that state exactly what is meant.
  - Replace direct statements with:
      deflection, control attempts, threat, bargaining, sarcasm, silence, mishearing.
  - Ensure each dialogue exchange has an agenda imbalance.
  - Add micro-interruptions (body movement, environment intrusion).
output_format:
  type: text
  structure:
    - "Revised chapter draft (dialogue improved)"
    - "Dialogue notes (bullets)"
quality_checks:
  - "No conversation exists only to inform the reader."
  - "At least one line per major exchange carries double meaning."
